# ase-fimd

Fourier-Integrator Molecular Dynamics (FIMD) workflows for ASE calculators.

## Install

```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Usage

```bash
fimd run --input molecule.xyz --calculator emt --band-min 0 --band-max 500 --output out
fimd run --input molecule.xyz --calculator emt --trajectory conv_md.traj \
    --basis-source covariance --band-min 0 --band-max 200 --output cov_out
fimd run-bands --input molecule.xyz --calculator mace_mp --bands "0:200,200:600,600:1200"
fimd calculators
```

`--basis-source covariance` builds the mode basis (W, Ω) from an external
conventional-MD trajectory rather than from a Hessian; it only takes effect
when `--trajectory` is also given.
